PT Kharisma Pemasaran Bersama
Nusantara , which sells  palm oil  from  Indonesia ’s state-owned
plantations, sold 3,000 metric tons of 5,250 tons that it
offered at an auction in Jakarta.  The following table lists the results of the sale today,
based on a faxed statement. The volumes are given in metric
tons, while prices are in rupiah per kilogram including a 10
percent value added tax, unless stated otherwise.  Indonesia is the world’s largest producer of palm oil.  To contact the reporter on this story:
